* Represents an operation upon two {@code long}-valued operands and producing a * {@code long}-valued result. This is the primitive type specialization of * {@link BinaryOperator} for {@code long}. * *

This is a functional interface * whose functional method is {@link #applyAsLong(long, long)}. * * @see BinaryOperator * @see LongUnaryOperator * @since 1.8

methods.name: long applyAsLong(long left, long right)
methods.comment:
* Applies this operator to the given operands.
